    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Centerboard sloops with mainsail and jib, usually 16 to 26 feet LOA (length overall), developed during the mid-nineteenth century around Muscongus Bay, Maine, for lobstering and fishing off the Maine and Massachusetts coasts; forerunners of Friendship sloops.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Balandra de quilla central con vela principal y foque, generalmente de 16 a 26 pies de longitud, desarrollado a mediados del siglo XIX en torno a la Bahía Muscongus, Maine, par la captura de la langosta y la pesca en las costas de Maine y Massachussets. Precursora de las goletas Friendship.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sloepen met midzwaard, grootzeil en kluiver, die meestal zo'n 4,9 tot 7,9 m lang zijn. Ze zijn halverwege de 19e eeuw in het gebied rond Muscongus Bay, in de Amerikaanse staat Maine, ontworpen om voor de kust van Maine en Massachusetts op kreeften en andere vis te kunnen vissen; voorlopers van Friendshipsloepen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>有主帆和艏三角帆的中鰭板單桅帆船，全長(LOA；length overall)通常為16至26英尺，發展於十九世紀美國緬因州的莫斯康格斯海灣(Muscongus Bay)，在緬因州和麻薩諸塞州沿岸地區用於捕龍蝦和魚類；是夫連希普單桅帆船(Friendship sloops)的前身。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
